  "title": "General Manager",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li>Manage project schedules, budgets, and resources to ensure timely and cost-effective completion</li><li>Oversee subcontractors, vendors, and on-site personnel</li><li>Ensure compliance with building codes, safety regulations, and company policies</li><li>Review and interpret construction drawings, specifications, and contracts</li><li>Identify and resolve project issues and risk</li><li>Prepare and maintain project documentation, reports, and schedules</li><li>Able to travel around Singapore based on site location<br /></li></ul><h3>Qualifications</h3><p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Construction Management, Engineering, or a related field (or equivalent experience)</li><li>3 years of experience in construction management or related roles</li><li>Excellent leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills</li><li>Proficiency in construction management software is preferred</li><li>Ability to read and interpret blueprints and technical documents</li></ul></p>",
